It took getting there,
to my own personal hell,

00:24:05.200 --> 00:24:07.990
for me to finally
have the strength

00:24:07.990 --> 00:24:13.342
and the courage to actually,
truly change my life.

00:24:13.342 --> 00:24:14.300
I do a lot of this now.

00:24:14.300 --> 00:24:15.700
I talk to a lot of
people, and I see

00:24:15.700 --> 00:24:17.992
that most, if not all people
are addicted to something.

00:24:17.992 --> 00:24:21.830
And some of it's maybe
better than others.

00:24:21.830 --> 00:24:23.770
But it could be
something like Facebook,

00:24:23.770 --> 00:24:26.012
or should I say Google?

00:24:26.012 --> 00:24:27.470
CAROLINE DEHNERT
MOYER: Technology.

00:24:27.470 --> 00:24:29.220
JAM ALKER: It could
be-- yeah, technology.

00:24:29.220 --> 00:24:29.963
It could be porn.

00:24:29.963 --> 00:24:32.380
It could be what's in your
pantry or in your refrigerator.

00:24:32.380 --> 00:24:33.010
Could be work.

00:24:33.010 --> 00:24:37.030
There might be a few workaholics
in this room right now.

00:24:37.030 --> 00:24:39.212
Now my disease of
addiction, as we'll

00:24:39.212 --> 00:24:41.170
talk about a little bit
further, came from some

00:24:41.170 --> 00:24:42.212
of the underlying trauma.

00:24:42.212 --> 00:24:42.950
I was miserable.

00:24:42.950 --> 00:24:43.690
I grew up miserable.

00:24:43.690 --> 00:24:45.982
There was something inside
of me that just never, ever,

00:24:45.982 --> 00:24:47.530
ever felt right.

00:24:47.530 --> 00:24:49.210
The reason why I
say I'm grateful

00:24:49.210 --> 00:24:51.017
is that if I wasn't
one of those people,

00:24:51.017 --> 00:24:52.600
if I was instead one
of the people who

00:24:52.600 --> 00:24:54.130
came home at the end
of the day miserable,

00:24:54.130 --> 00:24:55.547
and just flipped
on the television

00:24:55.547 --> 00:24:57.160
and zoned out until
I went to bed,

00:24:57.160 --> 00:24:59.260
and did it the next
day and the next day,

00:24:59.260 --> 00:25:02.770
I would have gone through my
whole life being miserable,

00:25:02.770 --> 00:25:06.160
But not quite miserable
enough to actually change.

00:25:09.840 --> 00:25:10.820
So I'm grateful.

00:25:10.820 --> 00:25:13.010
I'm grateful that this
thing took me to that place

00:25:13.010 --> 00:25:14.280
where I truly changed my life.

00:25:14.280 --> 00:25:16.610
And I have truly
changed my life.

00:25:16.610 --> 00:25:19.340
So talking about this
journey of recovery,

00:25:19.340 --> 00:25:23.120
it started for me four
and 1/2 years ago,

00:25:23.120 --> 00:25:27.630
curled up on a plastic
mattress in a detox facility.

00:25:27.630 --> 00:25:29.750
I was shaking.

00:25:29.750 --> 00:25:31.460
I was puking.

00:25:31.460 --> 00:25:33.800
My bones were aching.

00:25:33.800 --> 00:25:35.330
Dehydrated .

00:25:35.330 --> 00:25:40.940
This is what feeling dope sick
is, withdrawing from heroin.

00:25:40.940 --> 00:25:42.080
Numb.

00:25:42.080 --> 00:25:46.750
And I was shitting
myself, not figuratively,

00:25:46.750 --> 00:25:50.300
literally shitting myself
laying on this plastic mattress.

00:25:50.300 --> 00:25:52.300
And I remind myself of
that, and I talk about it

00:25:52.300 --> 00:25:53.570
in front of people all the time.

00:25:53.570 --> 00:25:55.070
It's important that
I talk about it.

00:25:55.070 --> 00:25:57.340
It's important that I
remind myself of that

00:25:57.340 --> 00:26:00.490
because the way this disease
of addiction works is it

00:26:00.490 --> 00:26:02.960
makes me want to believe that
I could go back out one more

00:26:02.960 --> 00:26:03.460
time.

00:26:03.460 --> 00:26:08.250
Just-- I'm sure that four and
1/2 years, that's a long time.

00:26:08.250 --> 00:26:09.790
I could probably be all right.

00:26:09.790 --> 00:26:11.830
Just one night of partying.

00:26:11.830 --> 00:26:13.660
How bad could that be?

00:26:13.660 --> 00:26:16.180
But I work a program
of recovery now.

00:26:16.180 --> 00:26:20.980
And because of that, I know that
if I were to do that, at best,

00:26:20.980 --> 00:26:24.130
at absolute best, I would end
up back on that plastic mattress

00:26:24.130 --> 00:26:25.420
in a detox facility.

00:26:25.420 --> 00:26:29.410
More likely, I
would end up dead.

00:26:29.410 --> 00:26:32.620
I would end up dead leaving
a beautiful, six-year-old

00:26:32.620 --> 00:26:35.950
daughter without a father.

00:26:35.950 --> 00:26:40.060
And my daughter, she
not only deserves

00:26:40.060 --> 00:26:41.710
to have a clean
and sober father.

00:26:41.710 --> 00:26:46.557
She deserves to have a
father that is above ground.

00:26:46.557 --> 00:26:48.640
But coming to terms with
that when I was out there

00:26:48.640 --> 00:26:50.120
was not easy.

00:26:50.120 --> 00:26:52.300
It was not easy to
concede this battle.

00:26:52.300 --> 00:26:54.280
Coming to terms with
that fact that I

00:26:54.280 --> 00:26:58.713
couldn't battle my disease
into submission was not easy.

00:26:58.713 --> 00:27:00.130
So the way I had
to look at it was

00:27:00.130 --> 00:27:02.470
like a nation that went to war.

00:27:02.470 --> 00:27:04.190
If a nation goes
to war, and they

00:27:04.190 --> 00:27:06.092
are fighting against
a superior opponent,

00:27:06.092 --> 00:27:08.050
they can fight, they can
fight, they can fight.

00:27:08.050 --> 00:27:11.200
No matter how hard they
fight, they cannot win.

00:27:11.200 --> 00:27:12.880
Superior opponent.

00:27:12.880 --> 00:27:14.170
Fight and fight, cannot win.

00:27:14.170 --> 00:27:16.190
They're left with two options.

00:27:16.190 --> 00:27:19.140
One is to die.

00:27:19.140 --> 00:27:23.610
Two is to surrender.

00:27:23.610 --> 00:27:27.320
And that's what finally
had to happen with me.

00:27:27.320 --> 00:27:30.170
Understanding the
disease of addiction,

00:27:30.170 --> 00:27:33.950
understanding that it
was a superior opponent

00:27:33.950 --> 00:27:36.620
that I could not beat.

00:27:36.620 --> 00:27:38.030
Die or surrender.

00:27:38.030 --> 00:27:40.550
Once I finally
surrendered to that,

00:27:40.550 --> 00:27:42.230
things finally started
to change for me.

00:27:45.520 --> 00:27:51.850
When I was 30 years old,
I had the record label.

00:27:51.850 --> 00:27:53.080
I had the recording studio.

00:27:53.080 --> 00:27:54.970
I had toured the
country, played in front

00:27:54.970 --> 00:27:57.940
of thousands of screaming fans.

00:27:57.940 --> 00:27:59.070
I had a lot of money.

00:27:59.070 --> 00:28:01.390
Wasn't quite a millionaire,
but I was well on my way.

00:28:01.390 --> 00:28:04.030
Had all of these things, these
things that people would say

00:28:04.030 --> 00:28:05.240
make you very successful.

00:28:05.240 --> 00:28:06.110
You're living your dreams.

00:28:06.110 --> 00:28:06.880
That's what I always wanted.

00:28:06.880 --> 00:28:08.390
I wanted to be a rock star,
I wanted to have money,

00:28:08.390 --> 00:28:09.932
I wanted to have
all of these things.

00:28:09.932 --> 00:28:12.850
And at 30 years old, I
became a heroin addict.

00:28:12.850 --> 00:28:15.310
At 30 years old,
I became a junkie

00:28:15.310 --> 00:28:18.720
having all of those things.

00:28:18.720 --> 00:28:20.120
How does that happen?

00:28:25.160 --> 00:28:30.410
All of this material success
and becoming a heroin addict,

00:28:30.410 --> 00:28:33.450
it happened because I
was miserable inside.

00:28:36.260 --> 00:28:38.220
I don't want to get into
a lot of the details,

00:28:38.220 --> 00:28:40.115
but there was a lot
of family trauma,

00:28:40.115 --> 00:28:43.040
the horribly
explosive upbringing.

00:28:43.040 --> 00:28:45.050
One of my first memories
in life is my dad

00:28:45.050 --> 00:28:49.250
walking towards me wide-eyed,
blood gushing down his face.

00:28:49.250 --> 00:28:50.810
Memory I can place
chronologically

00:28:50.810 --> 00:28:52.490
directly before
that, one of my mom

00:28:52.490 --> 00:28:54.230
smashing a whiskey
bottle over his head

00:28:54.230 --> 00:28:55.850
to stop his violent advances.

00:28:55.850 --> 00:28:59.460
The first time I got blackout
drunk I was seven years old.

00:28:59.460 --> 00:29:01.010
The first time I
smoked weed was also

00:29:01.010 --> 00:29:02.218
the first time I did cocaine.

00:29:02.218 --> 00:29:03.565
I was nine years old.

00:29:03.565 --> 00:29:04.940
By the time I was
in ninth grade,

00:29:04.940 --> 00:29:08.450
I had done everything
except for crack and heroin,

00:29:08.450 --> 00:29:11.430
by ninth grade.

00:29:11.430 --> 00:29:12.630
Why did I do these things?

00:29:12.630 --> 00:29:16.440
I was numbing myself to
that underlying pain, a pain

00:29:16.440 --> 00:29:18.810
that I didn't know
how to deal with.

00:29:18.810 --> 00:29:21.660
And I'd been told by
society that these things,

00:29:21.660 --> 00:29:23.280
these successes on
the outside world,

00:29:23.280 --> 00:29:25.320
were going to be the
things that fixed them.

00:29:25.320 --> 00:29:26.440
And they didn't.

00:29:26.440 --> 00:29:28.388
But at this point, I
didn't understand it.

00:29:28.388 --> 00:29:30.180
And I dropped deep into
a heroin addiction,

00:29:30.180 --> 00:29:32.763
and over the course of the next
five years, I lost everything.

00:29:32.763 --> 00:29:36.040
I lost all the money,
the recording studio,

00:29:36.040 --> 00:29:36.780
the record label.

00:29:36.780 --> 00:29:38.525
I lost all of these things.

00:29:38.525 --> 00:29:39.900
And at the point
where I was just

00:29:39.900 --> 00:29:44.542
about to pawn my guitar, which
was my last worldly possession,

00:29:44.542 --> 00:29:45.750
I decided I needed some help.

00:29:45.750 --> 00:29:46.670
I went to my doctor.

00:29:46.670 --> 00:29:47.940
He put me on some medication.

00:29:47.940 --> 00:29:49.565
He told me I needed
to go to treatment.

00:29:49.565 --> 00:29:51.300
I said no thank you, Dr. Cook.

00:29:51.300 --> 00:29:52.140
I'm not an addict.

00:29:52.140 --> 00:29:53.100
I don't need to go to treatment.

00:29:53.100 --> 00:29:54.087
I can figure this out.

00:29:54.087 --> 00:29:55.170
What are my other options?

00:29:55.170 --> 00:29:57.090
He said Jam, if you're not
going to go to treatment,

00:29:57.090 --> 00:29:59.507
at least you need to start
going to these 12 step meetings

00:29:59.507 --> 00:30:02.160
that you've heard of.

00:30:02.160 --> 00:30:04.440
To please him and to
please my loved ones,

00:30:04.440 --> 00:30:07.080
I went to a 12 step meeting at
a place called the Mustard Seed

00:30:07.080 --> 00:30:09.750
here in Chicago, a very famous
place where they hold these 12

00:30:09.750 --> 00:30:11.340
step fellowship meetings.

00:30:11.340 --> 00:30:13.365
I walked in, sat in
the back of the room,

00:30:13.365 --> 00:30:15.490
stayed away from everybody,
looked around the room.

00:30:15.490 --> 00:30:16.830
No, I'm not one of these people.

00:30:16.830 --> 00:30:17.740
There's no way.

00:30:17.740 --> 00:30:20.500
I'm not an addict, no.

00:30:20.500 --> 00:30:22.080
I just need to get
my shit together.

00:30:22.080 --> 00:30:23.850
I'll figure this out.

00:30:23.850 --> 00:30:26.790
I sat through the meeting
looking for all the differences

00:30:26.790 --> 00:30:29.340
rather than the similarities.

00:30:29.340 --> 00:30:31.390
By the end of the meeting,
I convinced myself

00:30:31.390 --> 00:30:32.710
I wasn't one of those people.

00:30:32.710 --> 00:30:34.440
I left the meeting
and I went back

00:30:34.440 --> 00:30:38.100
out for another seven years, the
worst seven years of my life,

00:30:38.100 --> 00:30:40.350
the worst seven years
of active addiction,

00:30:40.350 --> 00:30:43.920
the worst seven years
of being a junkie.

00:30:43.920 --> 00:30:46.100
Lost everything.

00:30:46.100 --> 00:30:47.100
Did horrible things.

00:30:47.100 --> 00:30:50.580
Lied to people, cheated,
stole, manipulated,

00:30:50.580 --> 00:30:54.870
whatever I needed to do
to get that next one.

00:30:54.870 --> 00:30:57.110
When I finally
did surrender four

00:30:57.110 --> 00:31:00.400
and 1/2 years ago, checked
myself into a treatment center,

00:31:00.400 --> 00:31:02.260
I still had this
ego inside of me.

00:31:02.260 --> 00:31:03.640
And I sat down
with my counselor.

00:31:03.640 --> 00:31:04.515
Her name was Nanette.

00:31:04.515 --> 00:31:09.520
I said, Nanette, I need you
to bottom line this for me.

00:31:09.520 --> 00:31:12.190
I know I'm in a unit
with 30 other guys,

00:31:12.190 --> 00:31:13.990
but I'm a lot smarter than them.

00:31:13.990 --> 00:31:15.560
I'm a lot more
successful than them.

00:31:15.560 --> 00:31:17.260
So I just need you to
sit here and bottom line

00:31:17.260 --> 00:31:18.718
it for me so I can
get out of here.

00:31:18.718 --> 00:31:20.240
I need you to give
me the secret.

00:31:20.240 --> 00:31:22.560
And she kind of laughed
at me, and she said, OK,

00:31:22.560 --> 00:31:24.310
what's the secret that
you're looking for?

00:31:24.310 --> 00:31:26.030
I was like, Nanette,
I need the secret.

00:31:26.030 --> 00:31:28.030
You just need to tell me
how to stop doing drugs

00:31:28.030 --> 00:31:28.947
and I'll be on my way.

00:31:28.947 --> 00:31:31.960
And she laughed at
me, and she said, Jam,

00:31:31.960 --> 00:31:35.360
drugs are not your problem.

00:31:35.360 --> 00:31:37.980
Drugs are not your problem.

00:31:37.980 --> 00:31:40.942
And I said Nanette, I have just
checked myself into a rehab.

00:31:40.942 --> 00:31:42.650
I've just checked
myself into a treatment

00:31:42.650 --> 00:31:43.820
center for drug addiction.

00:31:43.820 --> 00:31:45.590
Of course drugs are my problem.

00:31:45.590 --> 00:31:47.420
That is why I'm here.

00:31:47.420 --> 00:31:50.030
And she said, Jam, drugs
are not your problem.

00:31:50.030 --> 00:31:52.430
Drugs are your solution
to your problem.

00:31:56.190 --> 00:31:57.990
Drugs are not my problem.

00:31:57.990 --> 00:32:01.190
Drugs were my solution
to my problem.

00:32:01.190 --> 00:32:04.920
And thinking back on it, it's
horrible fucking solution

00:32:04.920 --> 00:32:05.680
to the problem.

00:32:05.680 --> 00:32:07.830
It didn't work.

00:32:07.830 --> 00:32:10.530
All evidence was
to the contrary.

00:32:10.530 --> 00:32:14.820
But this disease makes
you keep going back there.

00:32:14.820 --> 00:32:17.100
Now I hear this
all the time now,

00:32:17.100 --> 00:32:19.680
being surrounded by recovery,
the drugs are not your problem.

00:32:19.680 --> 00:32:21.040
Drugs are your solution
to your problem.

00:32:21.040 --> 00:32:23.280
But at that time, it was
the first time I heard it.

00:32:23.280 --> 00:32:24.760
And it was mind-blowing.

00:32:24.760 --> 00:32:26.520
It was an epiphany
kind of moment.

00:32:26.520 --> 00:32:28.050
Yes.

00:32:28.050 --> 00:32:29.290
Drugs are not my problem.

00:32:29.290 --> 00:32:31.020
They are the solution
to my problem.

00:32:31.020 --> 00:32:34.020
My problem was me.

00:32:34.020 --> 00:32:38.060
My problem was
that I kept trying

00:32:38.060 --> 00:32:41.210
to solve what was
going on inside of me

00:32:41.210 --> 00:32:42.780
with things in
the outside world,

00:32:42.780 --> 00:32:49.130
whether it was fame, ego,
money, girls, relationships.

00:32:49.130 --> 00:32:50.597
I had this empty
hole inside of me.

00:32:50.597 --> 00:32:52.430
No matter what I did
to try to fill it with,

00:32:52.430 --> 00:32:54.555
those outside things, I
always woke up the next day

00:32:54.555 --> 00:32:57.185
with that empty hole.

00:32:57.185 --> 00:32:58.060
And I think about it.

00:32:58.060 --> 00:33:00.310
You know, this is something
we're conditioned towards,

00:33:00.310 --> 00:33:02.417
right, from the
moment as kids we turn

00:33:02.417 --> 00:33:05.000
our attention to the television,
to the internet, to anything,

00:33:05.000 --> 00:33:08.060
we are told to buy, buy our
way out of our problems.

00:33:08.060 --> 00:33:09.140
We become consumers.

00:33:09.140 --> 00:33:11.010
We're told when we're
kids to buy this toy

00:33:11.010 --> 00:33:12.177
and life's going to be good.

00:33:12.177 --> 00:33:14.570
Buy this game, things
will be good as teenagers.

00:33:14.570 --> 00:33:15.950
Buy these shoes
or these clothes,

00:33:15.950 --> 00:33:16.640
you're going to fit in.

00:33:16.640 --> 00:33:18.890
As adults, you buy this
house, you get this job,

00:33:18.890 --> 00:33:20.630
you're going to be happy.

00:33:20.630 --> 00:33:22.160
This is what we're taught.

00:33:22.160 --> 00:33:25.100
And for someone like me, I
feel like I never had a chance.

00:33:25.100 --> 00:33:26.800
Being as miserable
inside as I was,

00:33:26.800 --> 00:33:29.300
I don't think there's some kind
of big conspiracy out there.

00:33:29.300 --> 00:33:32.000
But companies need to
sell their products,

00:33:32.000 --> 00:33:34.382
so they need to tell you
that you're miserable,

00:33:34.382 --> 00:33:36.590
and if you buy their stuff,
you're going to be happy.

00:33:36.590 --> 00:33:37.900
And I was miserable.

00:33:37.900 --> 00:33:41.032
And I bought into that
time and time again.

00:33:41.032 --> 00:33:42.740
And again, this is
one of the reasons why

00:33:42.740 --> 00:33:46.070
I'm so grateful that I
was taken to these depths

00:33:46.070 --> 00:33:48.100
because it was in a
place like treatment

00:33:48.100 --> 00:33:54.770
where Nanette said to me
that the problem was me, not

00:33:54.770 --> 00:33:55.270
the drugs.

00:33:59.313 --> 00:34:00.730
So when I was
there, and I started

00:34:00.730 --> 00:34:02.710
to listen to the people
who had what I wanted,

00:34:02.710 --> 00:34:05.680
people who were far
smarter than me, finally

00:34:05.680 --> 00:34:08.320
did surrender, and
turned that light

00:34:08.320 --> 00:34:12.620
inward rather than shining
it outward for the answers,

00:34:12.620 --> 00:34:15.040
my life truly started to change.

00:34:15.040 --> 00:34:19.780
I started to heal some of
those underlying traumas.

00:34:19.780 --> 00:34:24.190
Recovery is not about
abstaining from drugs,

00:34:24.190 --> 00:34:26.650
abstaining from alcohol.

00:34:26.650 --> 00:34:31.840
Recovery is about rebuilding
your life, your inner world,

00:34:31.840 --> 00:34:33.940
in a way that you
are happy enough

00:34:33.940 --> 00:34:38.389
that you don't need
to numb yourself

00:34:38.389 --> 00:34:43.010
through drugs, through alcohol,
through porn, through food,

00:34:43.010 --> 00:34:46.159
through work, through gambling,
through any of these things.

00:34:46.159 --> 00:34:49.670
That is what recovery is about,
healing that underlying trauma,

00:34:49.670 --> 00:34:52.730
whatever it might be, so we
can stop that numbing behavior.

00:34:57.670 --> 00:34:59.410
I'm going to end with this.

00:35:02.900 --> 00:35:05.590
As I said, my life is surrounded
by recovery these days,

00:35:05.590 --> 00:35:07.560
so I spend a lot of
time hearing stories

00:35:07.560 --> 00:35:11.140
from my brothers and sisters in
recovery of their backgrounds,

00:35:11.140 --> 00:35:13.050
their upbringings,
their stories that

00:35:13.050 --> 00:35:14.730
brought them to their knees.

00:35:14.730 --> 00:35:19.080
And I see or hear about some
horrible, horrible, tragic

00:35:19.080 --> 00:35:22.470
things that they've done,
that they've been through,

00:35:22.470 --> 00:35:26.040
that they've used to cope with
the hand they've been dealt.

00:35:26.040 --> 00:35:31.800
Now my story does not
include any jail time.

00:35:31.800 --> 00:35:34.770
My story does not
include any homelessness.

00:35:39.480 --> 00:35:42.030
That is the way in which my
story may be a little different

00:35:42.030 --> 00:35:43.905
than some of the other
stories you might hear

00:35:43.905 --> 00:35:46.560
told by folks who have been
through similar experiences

00:35:46.560 --> 00:35:48.520
to me and are now in recovery.

00:35:48.520 --> 00:35:50.270
So those are the
ways that my story

00:35:50.270 --> 00:35:52.770
might be a little different
than the other ones you'll hear.

00:35:52.770 --> 00:35:54.930
But I have a friend
of mine who is also

00:35:54.930 --> 00:35:56.850
in this 12 step
fellowship who taught

00:35:56.850 --> 00:36:00.540
me to find the similarities
and to stay away

00:36:00.540 --> 00:36:02.430
from the differences.

00:36:02.430 --> 00:36:06.540
And the way that I am the
same as every other person

00:36:06.540 --> 00:36:09.210
in recovery, the way that I am
the same as every person who

00:36:09.210 --> 00:36:11.730
is still in their
active addiction--

00:36:11.730 --> 00:36:15.030
the way that we're are the same
is that we have a disease that

00:36:15.030 --> 00:36:18.060
wants to kill us.

00:36:18.060 --> 00:36:23.660
I have a disease that
wants to kill me.

00:36:23.660 --> 00:36:26.000
But because of the
recovery program

00:36:26.000 --> 00:36:30.170
that I work, because I come
and do things like this,

00:36:30.170 --> 00:36:33.140
because I keep myself
involved, because I

00:36:33.140 --> 00:36:36.260
am of service to others, giving
of myself, asking nothing

00:36:36.260 --> 00:36:41.210
in return, I get what we
refer to as a daily reprieve

00:36:41.210 --> 00:36:43.970
from the disease of addiction.

00:36:43.970 --> 00:36:46.280
And because of that,
I can confidently

00:36:46.280 --> 00:36:51.770
say to you and to my disease,
it will not kill me today.

00:36:51.770 --> 00:36:52.687
Thanks.

