00:43:53.800 --> 00:43:55.440
JAM ALKER: Yeah, it's
a great question.

00:43:55.440 --> 00:43:55.620
AUDIENCE: OK.

00:43:55.620 --> 00:43:57.960
So please help me understand
how you manage that.

00:43:57.960 --> 00:44:02.320
JAM ALKER: So what
you're taught in recovery

00:44:02.320 --> 00:44:06.310
is if you are truly working
a program of recovery,

00:44:06.310 --> 00:44:09.880
that the obsession to
use should be lifted.

00:44:09.880 --> 00:44:13.400
The compulsion to
use will be lifted.

00:44:13.400 --> 00:44:16.270
It's one of the things
that's called the promises

00:44:16.270 --> 00:44:19.840
within certain fellowships.

00:44:19.840 --> 00:44:22.180
Would I have toured in the
first year of my recovery?

00:44:22.180 --> 00:44:23.860
Absolutely not.

00:44:23.860 --> 00:44:26.800
But I am at the
point in my recovery

00:44:26.800 --> 00:44:31.900
where I am comfortable being
in a bar, being around alcohol.

00:44:31.900 --> 00:44:34.540
Do I allow myself to be
surrounded with drugs?

00:44:34.540 --> 00:44:36.470
No, absolutely not.

00:44:39.500 --> 00:44:42.190
But people who are doing
drugs or using drugs

00:44:42.190 --> 00:44:43.753
can pretty quickly get a vibe.

00:44:43.753 --> 00:44:45.170
When they know
you're in recovery,

00:44:45.170 --> 00:44:47.670
they're not about to try to do
those things in front of you.

00:44:47.670 --> 00:44:50.500
But as far as being around
weed or being around alcohol,

00:44:50.500 --> 00:44:55.400
I'm around it quite a
bit when out on the road.

00:44:55.400 --> 00:44:56.590
But I work a program.

00:44:56.590 --> 00:45:00.520
I really, truly have done
the work to understand.

00:45:00.520 --> 00:45:03.910
One of the simple CBT,
cognitive behavioral therapy

00:45:03.910 --> 00:45:07.280
things they teach you early
on is play the tape forward.

00:45:07.280 --> 00:45:09.430
It's like what I talked
about, how I would end up

00:45:09.430 --> 00:45:11.890
on that plastic mattress in
a detox facility, or more

00:45:11.890 --> 00:45:13.120
likely, dead.

00:45:13.120 --> 00:45:17.140
I know where that will lead me.

00:45:17.140 --> 00:45:19.190
And I have this
amazing life now.

00:45:19.190 --> 00:45:20.310
And I don't mean that--

00:45:20.310 --> 00:45:24.883
I have a lot of amazing
outside things happening.

00:45:24.883 --> 00:45:27.050
Financially, with my music
career, with my speaking,

00:45:27.050 --> 00:45:28.680
these are amazing things.

00:45:28.680 --> 00:45:30.800
But I have this
amazing life because

00:45:30.800 --> 00:45:36.830
of what's happened inside of me,
this psychic, spiritual change

00:45:36.830 --> 00:45:39.740
that has occurred inside of
me, turning that light inside.

00:45:39.740 --> 00:45:41.093
I don't want to lose this.

00:45:41.093 --> 00:45:42.260
This is the most important--

00:45:42.260 --> 00:45:45.180
I'm happy for the
first time in my life.

00:45:45.180 --> 00:45:48.530
And I know where that will
lead me, and it's just--

00:45:48.530 --> 00:45:50.270
it's not appealing.

00:45:50.270 --> 00:45:51.950
It's not an answer, right?

00:45:51.950 --> 00:45:53.460
It was not the problem.

00:45:53.460 --> 00:45:55.610
It was my shitty
solution to the problem.

00:45:55.610 --> 00:45:56.780
And I know that now.

00:45:56.780 --> 00:46:00.796
I know that at my core.

00:46:00.796 --> 00:46:02.483
Does that make sense?

00:46:02.483 --> 00:46:04.150
CAROLINE DEHNERT
MOYER: I would chime in

00:46:04.150 --> 00:46:05.358
