00:54:51.900 --> 00:54:52.710
AUDIENCE: No.

00:54:52.710 --> 00:54:54.060
JAM ALKER: Thank God.

00:54:54.060 --> 00:54:55.567
AUDIENCE: Trenton, New Jersey.

00:54:55.567 --> 00:54:56.150
JAM ALKER: OK.

00:54:56.150 --> 00:54:58.340
Not much better, but yeah.

00:54:58.340 --> 00:55:04.760
That's a lot of opiate
addiction happening out there.

00:55:04.760 --> 00:55:06.900
CAROLINE DEHNERT MOYER:
But Gabby, for you,

00:55:06.900 --> 00:55:10.580
as the sister, what
I would say is--

00:55:10.580 --> 00:55:14.610
I do this-- I think I did it
with my brother even this week.

00:55:14.610 --> 00:55:15.520
I go hey, Carl.

00:55:15.520 --> 00:55:16.770
I know you don't work Mondays.

00:55:16.770 --> 00:55:18.710
You want to come
over for dinner?

00:55:18.710 --> 00:55:21.000
And I actually got a
response, but usually I

00:55:21.000 --> 00:55:21.940
don't get a response.

00:55:21.940 --> 00:55:24.730
But I call it trickling love.

00:55:24.730 --> 00:55:28.770
And I don't expect much
back, but I just trickle it

00:55:28.770 --> 00:55:30.840
out there, like I'm still here.

00:55:30.840 --> 00:55:32.370
I still love you.

00:55:32.370 --> 00:55:37.380
But you have to be able to know
you might not get stuff back.

00:55:37.380 --> 00:55:40.470
But it feels good to do it
because it feels good for you

00:55:40.470 --> 00:55:44.650
to express and reach out.

00:55:44.650 --> 00:55:46.020
AUDIENCE: Thank you.

00:55:46.020 --> 00:55:48.270
CAROLINE DEHNERT MOYER:
There's a question on the Dory

